# Force Mockito to use the subclass mock-maker instead of the default
# inline mock-maker (Mockito 5.x default).
#
# Why: the inline mock-maker uses class redefinition via a dynamically
# attached Java agent (ByteBuddy). On JDK 21+ this triggers warnings,
# and in some CI environments (notably GitHub Actions runners) the
# redefinition outright fails with:
#
#   MockitoException: Could not modify all classes
#     [interface org.keycloak.authentication.AuthenticationFlowContext,
#      interface org.keycloak.authentication.AbstractAuthenticationFlowContext]
#
# We never need to mock final classes, enums, or static methods here -
# every @Mock in this module targets either an interface
# (AuthenticationFlowContext, KeycloakSession, RealmModel, etc.) or a
# non-final concrete class (EventBuilder). The subclass mock-maker
# handles both without touching the Instrumentation API, so dynamic
# agent loading is sidestepped entirely.
#
# Refs:
#   - https://javadoc.io/doc/org.mockito/mockito-core/latest/org/mockito/MockMakers.html
#   - https://github.com/mockito/mockito/issues/3037 (JDK 21 agent warning)
mock-maker-subclass
